title: Calibration Downloading

body.body: Calibration Downloads - ECM Status Based Download Scan
Always ensure that the correct motorcycle model name is identified and displayed before starting a calibration download.
Downloading calibrations for an incorrect model may cause motorcycle electronic systems to function incorrectly.
This can cause an unsafe riding condition which could lead to an accident resulting in injury or death.
Always ensure that the correct motorcycle market variant is identified and displayed before starting a calibration download.
Downloading calibrations for an incorrect market variant may cause motorcycle electrical or electronic systems to function incorrectly for your region.

body.body: If the scan successfully detects an individual model and market variant, the model confirmation screen is displayed.
This screen will show the Model Name, Market Variant and VIN detected along with a list of applicable markets.
Check the model name and market variant details displayed are correct for your model and region.

Download Failure and Failed Download Recovery
If a download failure occurs, the following screen will be displayed.
Before attempting to restart the download:
Turn the motorcycle ignition Off for at least 60 seconds, then turn the ignition On.
Make sure all other motorcycle ECMs are up to date and have the correct calibration installed for the model and market variant.
Follow the process above to restart the download.
The motorcycle scan process will attempt to identify the connected motorcycle from data obtained from other ECMs. However, it may not be possible to identify the exact model and market variant.
